  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In left-sided colon and rectal cancer, the occurrence of synchronous para-aortic lymph node&#xD;
      metastasis is rare, with the incidence of being approximate 1-2%. Currently, there has been&#xD;
      no standard treatment strategy for this situation. The present trial is designed to evaluate&#xD;
      the safety and efficacy of para-aortic lymph node dissection for left-sided colon and rectal&#xD;
      cancer with synchronous para-aortic lymph node metastasis&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
